incidents.name: Issues with the Traces and Spans API

incident_updates.body: We experienced issues with the Traces and Spans API between 15:43 UTC and 16:00 UTC. There may be data loss in your performance metrics for this time period, although BugSnag's Performance SDKs will retry sending trace and span data.

incidents.name: Issues with the Error Reporting API

incident_updates.body: We experienced a spike in traffic between 19:47 UTC and 19:51 UTC, which caused issues with the Error Reporting API. There may be gaps in your events for this time period, although some platform specific notifiers will retry sending events.

This issue will have affected mapping files uploaded between 09:32 UTC yesterday and 13:00 UTC today, causing any events relying on those source maps to not symbolicate properly and create new groupings. This is now resolved, so any uploaded mapping files, including those uploaded in that time frame, will now successfully symbolicate any new events. Unfortunately old events affected by this will not be symbolicated retroactively, but any new events with matching source maps will be symbolicated and return to their previous error groupings.
